RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 54. Claiming Purse 21800. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allo wed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAY MAYS CASTLE settled in the three and four paths of the opening turn, challenged leaving the three eighths pole and took over between horses past the five sixteenths, dueled clear midway on the far turn, widened at the rail, was kept alert to deep stretch then taken in hand late yards. APPEALING ROAD rated just off the pace in the four and five paths on the first turn, closed to the lead approaching the three eighths pole but was met past the five sixteenths, rounded the far turn off the rail and had to settle for second best. PETTYFORURTHOUGHTS stalked the earlier pace two deep, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail then flattened in the lane. GOLDEN SALLY rated close inside on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail, angled out toward the eighth pole but showed little in the lane. WAGER WORTHY stalked three wide on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but faded at the rail on the far turn. PHILMARY CASTLE set the early pace inside, was met approaching the three eighths pole and faded past the five sixteenths. HOOK THE CHAIN saved ground on the first turn, eased outward past the half mile pole but showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: Golden Sally
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close inside,bid 3/8,off rail far turn,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Starter Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS SINCE MARCH 24, 2021. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 24 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since January 24 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where En tered For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ THE REASON took a quick lead and rated the early pace inside, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths pole and was steadily handled through the stretch. CRUZ IN THE CASTLE gave chase, raced in the three path on the turn and cleared second later yards. DING DING engaged in close chase, challenged at the five sixteenths pole but dropped back midway on the turn and flattened the final sixteenth. SALSA RITA chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. UNCANNY engaged in close early chase, steadied between horses approaching the five sixteenths pole, rounded the turn near the rail and weakened in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 16900. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE SEPTEMBER 24, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since September 24 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, al lowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARVELLA NASTY rated the pace inside, kept the edge over Miss Wild leaving the three eighths pole, cleared that one approaching the quarter, widened at the rail on the far turn then geared down the final sixteenth. SHINY PENNY settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase into the backstretch, raced in the three path of the far turn and came along for second inside the sixteenth pole. MISS WILD stalked the earlier pace three wide, challenged nearing the three eighths pole but dropped back approaching the quarter, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. FLOATING BY angled to the inside and settled off the pace, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened in the lane. SWEET ANNABELLA raced three wide on the opening turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. RAVENEL rounded the first turn four wide and left the turn outside, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole and raced wide on the far turn. SOME IS NINE stalked off the rail, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded toward the quarter. SHEMADEMELUCKY raced five wide on the first turn, left the turn outside and showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Marvella Nasty
ENTRY.OWNER: Bush Racing Stable and Liberty House Racing
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,kept edge from 3/8,widened turn,geared down1/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOBBYS CASE LOAD chased through the backstretch and raced close in the five path on the turn, dueled from the head of the lane and took over later yards. JUST A FLIRT chased the pace, rounded the turn in the three and four paths and was outfinished in the duel through the stretch. WINDSOR'S STAR pressured the pace inside and took the lead nearing the three eighths pole, dueled at even terms from the five sixteenths, contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn but flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. KING KJARTAN raced with the pace while tapering toward the inside, dueled at even terms from the five sixteenths pole, contested at a close disadvantage two deep on the turn but flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. DE'S CASTLE gave chase, rounded the turn about the five path and finished evenly to pass rivals. ALLEGHENY HERO chased inside, raced off the rail on the turn, lacked an opening and altered course near mid-stretch and finished well. JUBA'S YANKEE ONE chased inside, rounded the turn near the rail, eased outward into the lane then flattened stride inside the sixteenth pole. CURB THAT TIGER chased through the backstretch, raced off the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. JUBAY gave chase outside and never factored. SWEET T gave early chase outside then saved some ground on the turn. The remainder of tonights' card was cancelled due to inclement weather and poor track conditions.

ENTRY.NAME: Allegheny Hero
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,off rail turn,altered course 1/16,finished well
